  "description": "The structural skeleton — the calcium carbonate matrix that everything else grows on. Pulse src1 (narrowed PW=0.3, giving a crisper, more structural tone) against Saw src2 at +2 semitones detune (close collision, barely audible beating). proc1=LP (3200 Hz, low reso) — Pulse framework stays structurally bright; proc2=LP (950 Hz, reso=0.32) — Saw fills the mid-foundation register. fmDepth=0.15: minimal FM, structural integrity maintained. srcMix=0.45. Mono with short glide (0.04s) for legato framework lines. Mod: Env->proc2Cutoff (Saw foundation breathes), LFO->FXMix, Velocity->FilterCutoff, Aftertouch->Volume.",
